ArcGUI installation instructions
--------------------------------

ArcGUI is a prototype user interface client for the ARC1 libarcclient library.
The client is implemented in Python using the wxPython user interface toolkit.

Requirements
------------

GTK
wxWidgets (wxGTK)
wxPython
ARC1 client library of a recent bleeding edge version :)
ARC1 python binding for the client library

Installation
------------

Untar the tarball in a suitable location:

$ tar xvzf arcgui-x.y.tar.gz

Modify the arcgui start script:

$ cd arcgui-x.y/bin
$ [insert favourite editor here] arcgui

Modify the varibles in the script according to your installation.

arcgui-x.y/bin/arcgui:

#!/bin/sh
export ARC_LOCATION={Location of the ARC1 directory}
export ARCGUI_LOCATION={Location where the arcgui-tarball was unpacked}
export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:$ARC_LOCATION/lib64/python2.4/site-packages:$ARCGUI_LOCATION
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$ARC_LOCATION/lib64:$ARC_LOCATION/lib: ...
       $ARC_LOCATION/lib/arc:$ARC_LOCATION/lib64/python2.4/site-packages: ...
       $GLOBUS_LOCATION/lib
python $ARCGUI_LOCATION/arcgui.py

The lib64/python2.4 parts of the script must also be changed to match the
architecture and python version of the system. The above script was created
for a CentOS 5.3 x86_64 installation.

Finally add the $ARCGUI_LOCATION/bin to your search path.

Usage
-----

If everything was setup correctly the user interface can be started by typing:

$ arcgui

The client will create configuration files in ~/.arc if they don't exist or
use the same files as the other arc-tools (client.xml and jobs.xml). A sample
client.xml configuration is shown below:

~/.arc/client.xml:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ArcConfig>
  <DefaultServices>
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="index">ldap://index1.swegrid.se:2135/Mds-Vo-name=SweGrid,o=grid</URL>
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="index">ldap://index2.swegrid.se:2135/Mds-Vo-name=SweGrid,o=grid</URL>
  </DefaultServices>
  <TimeOut>20</TimeOut>
  <Broker>
    <Name>RandomBroker</Name>
  </Broker>
  <CACertificatePath>/etc/grid-certificates</CACertificatePath>
  <CertificatePath>/home/jonas/.globus/usercert.pem</CertificatePath>
  <KeyPath>/home/jonas/.globus/userkey.pem</KeyPath>
  <ProxyPath>/tmp/x509up_u500</ProxyPath>
</ArcConfig>

